Defendant Daniel R Gardner in court with attorney Mark E. Kershek.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Katrina Seipel and Atty. Lucas Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 1 and 2 are dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the following

Imposed and Stayed Sentence:

90 days Jail Straight Time (Credit - 15 days)

Term of Probation: 3 years

Conditions of probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Be involved in a 12 step program 2 times per week commencing within 30 days and obtain a mentor/sponsor within 60 days;
- Complete a Cognitive Thinking Course;
- Maintain a valid driver's license; 
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- No contact with Tammy M.K..  Agent can evaluate after 6 months.
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.


Costs:343.00  BAIL TO APPLY
DNA Surcharge: $200.00
Costs to be paid at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing 9-1-15

